The input images will measure exactly 600px x 600 px. To determine the overall texture of an image, I divide the image into squares which measure 3x3 pixels. From each pixel in the square, I calculate the grayscale value. After that, the minimum and maximum greyscale value is calculated for each square. Finally, the difference is defined as maximum - minimum. This difference is calculated for each 3x3 square in the image. The sum is then made of all those difference values, which gives us the &#39;Texture&#39;. The higher this sum of differences, the higher the texture in the image. Please see Photo 2 for more info.

First, a pixel, a square and an image are defined in Swift:

    struct Pixel {
